   <text>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0025.xml"/>William Allwood</persName></head>
         <opener><placeName>Rye, in Sussex</placeName><lb/><date when="1758-10-15">October 15,
               1758</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>My Dear Brother,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>It is very difficult to determine suddenly whether a person is or is not renewed. If
                  <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0971.xml"/>sister Hatton</persName> is, it
            will appear more and more clearly. If she is not, let her earnestly and patiently wait
            for it. I wrote to sister <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0909.xml"/>Ruth
               Hall</persName> and hope she will find time to send me an answer.</p>
         <p>The books you will, I suppose, receive shortly, if you have not already. <persName><ptr
                  target="/persons/pers2038.xml"/>Thomas Tobias</persName> is a serious man and will
            not do the work of the Lord deceitfully. If you see good, let brother <persName><ptr
                  target="/persons/pers0793.xml"/>Gibbs</persName> go at any time into
               <placeName>Lincolnshire</placeName>, and <persName><ptr
                  target="/persons/pers0896.xml"/>John Hacking</persName><note place="foot" n="1"
                     ><persName><ptr target="/persons/pers0896.xml"/>John Hacking</persName>, an
                  <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerant</seg> since at least <date when="1755"
               >1755</date>, had been appointed to <placeName>Lincolnshire</placeName> at the <date
                  when="1758">1758</date> Conference; see 10:287 in this edn.</note> come to you in
            his place.</p>
         <p>I believe another preacher will come from <placeName>London</placeName>, but
                  <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers1439.xml"/>Thomas Mitchell</persName> cannot
            yet be spared from these parts. There has never been any preaching in this county
            before, and now the kingdom of God is come upon them unawares.</p>
         <closer>O Billy, be much in prayer! I am,<lb/>
            <signed>Your affectionate friend and brother,<lb/><persName>J.
               Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
   </text>
</TEI>
